#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If you have control over the "
#~ "package where the type is defined, "
#~ "you can simply make the struct has"
#~ " `pub(all)` visibility."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "`a/a.mbt"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "pub(all) struct T {\n"
#~ "  mut value : Int\n"
#~ "}"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "However, this might not be the "
#~ "best solution if you want to hide"
#~ " the implementation details of the "
#~ "struct or protect the invariant of "
#~ "the struct. We recommend using "
#~ "getter/setter pattern to guard the "
#~ "access to the struct fields."
#~ msgstr ""

